Interface Summary
Message A bare ADT for defining the structure of a Message object as used by the server to communicate its working back to the client.
 

Class Summary
Client This is a client interface for interacting with a corresponding Server.
MessageImpl This is an implementation of the Message interface which allows the server to communicate its working with the client.
Server This is a Runnable Server Interface which can be executed in a thread by another class.
ServerBootstrap This class provides a caching thread pool which creates an instance of the server class to process user input as it is received by the system.
 

Package com.cs313.ace2 Description

This application aims to deliver a client and server which are able to interact with each other to demonstrate a user input being transfered from a client to server. A process being carried upon the input given, and an output being returned to the client system. The client then outputs the response and the application concludes. This verison attempts to implement the above in a threaded manner so that more than one client may access the server at any one time.
